__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the table or table number depending on the parameter passed

__ENTITIES.name: Field
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the field or a field number according to the parameters passed

__ENTITIES.name: Get last table number
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the highest table number among the tables in the database.

__ENTITIES.name: Get last field number
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get last field number ( tableNum | tablePtr ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the highest field number among the fields in the table whose number or pointer you pass in tableNum or tablePtr.

__ENTITIES.name: Table name
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the table whose number or pointer you pass in tableNum or tablePtr.

__ENTITIES.name: Field name
__ENTITIES.syntax: Field name ( fieldPtr | tableNum {; fieldNum} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the field whose pointer you pass in fieldPtr or whose table and field number you pass in tableNum and fieldNum.

__ENTITIES.name: GET FIELD PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET FIELD PROPERTIES ( fieldPtr | tableNum {; fieldNum}; fieldType {; fieldLength {; indexed {; unique {; invisible}}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the field specified by fieldPtr or by tableNum and fieldNum.

__ENTITIES.name: Count parameters
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of parameters passed to a project method.

__ENTITIES.name: SELECTION TO ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: SELECTION TO ARRAY {( aField | aTable ; array {; aField ; array {; aField2 ; array2 ; ... ; aFieldN ; arrayN}}{; *})}
__ENTITIES.description: Creates one or more arrays and copies data in the fields or record numbers from the current selection into the arrays.

__ENTITIES.name: ARRAY TO SELECTION
__ENTITIES.syntax: ARRAY TO SELECTION {( array ; aField {; array2 ; aField2 ; ... ; arrayN ; aFieldN}{; *} )}
__ENTITIES.description: Copies one or more arrays into a selection of records.

__ENTITIES.name: RELATE MANY
__ENTITIES.description: Establishes all One-to-Many relations for oneTable or establishes the One-to-Many relation for oneField

__ENTITIES.name: OLD RELATED MANY
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the selection of the related table, and selects the first record of the selection as the current record.

__ENTITIES.name: Open document
__ENTITIES.syntax: Open document ( document {; fileType}{; mode} ) -> DocRef
__ENTITIES.description: Opens the document whose name or pathname you pass in document.

__ENTITIES.name: Append document
__ENTITIES.description: Opens a document on disk.

__ENTITIES.name: Create document
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new document and returns its document reference number.

__ENTITIES.name: CLOSE DOCUMENT
__ENTITIES.description: Closes the document specified by docRef.

__ENTITIES.name: SET TIMEOUT
__ENTITIES.description: Specifies how much time a serial port command has to complete.

__ENTITIES.name: ACCEPT
__ENTITIES.description: Performs the same action as when the user presses the Enter key.

__ENTITIES.name: CANCEL
__ENTITIES.description: In the context of data entry, performs the same action as when the user presses the cancel key (Esc). Can also be placed in the optional close box method of a window created by the Open window command.

__ENTITIES.name: OBJECT SET COLOR
__ENTITIES.syntax: OBJECT SET COLOR ( {* ;} object ; color {; altColor} )
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the foreground and background colors of the form objects specified by object.

__ENTITIES.name: Is in set
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the current record of the table is in set, and returns FALSE if the current record of the table is not in set.

__ENTITIES.name: Size of array
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of elements in array.

__ENTITIES.name: Printing page
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the printing page number.

__ENTITIES.name: FORM Get current page
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of the currently displayed form page or of the current form loaded by the OPEN PRINTING FORM command.

__ENTITIES.name: QUERY
__ENTITIES.description: Looks for records matching the criteria specified in queryArgument and returns a selection of records for aTable.

__ENTITIES.name: Focus object
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the object having the focus in the current form.

__ENTITIES.name: ARRAY PICTURE
__ENTITIES.description: Creates and/or resizes an array of Picture elements in memory.

__ENTITIES.name: ARRAY POINTER
__ENTITIES.description: Creates or resizes an array of Pointer elements in memory.

__ENTITIES.name: EDIT ACCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Lets the user edit the password system.

__ENTITIES.name: C_LONGINT
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Long Integer variable.

__ENTITIES.name: C_TEXT
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Text variable.

__ENTITIES.name: C_REAL
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Real variable.

__ENTITIES.name: C_PICTURE
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Picture variable.

__ENTITIES.name: ARRAY TO LIST
__ENTITIES.syntax: ARRAY TO LIST ( array ; list {; itemRefs} )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates or replaces the hierarchical list or the choice list (created in the List editor) that is specified in list using the elements of the array array.

__ENTITIES.name: LIST TO ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: LIST TO ARRAY ( list ; array {; itemRefs} )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates or overrides the array array with the first level items of the list or choice list designated by list.

__ENTITIES.name: CHANGE CURRENT USER
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the identity of the current user in the database, without needing to quit.

__ENTITIES.name: PLAY
__ENTITIES.description: Plays sound files or, on OS X, a system sound

__ENTITIES.name: QUIT 4D
__ENTITIES.description: Exits the current 4D application and returns to the Desktop.

__ENTITIES.name: QUERY BY EXAMPLE
__ENTITIES.description: Displays the current input form as a query window

__ENTITIES.name: Is a variable
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if the pointer you pass in aPointer references a defined variable.

__ENTITIES.name: Type
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a numeric value that indicates the type of field or variable you have passed in the fieldVar parameter

__ENTITIES.name: FLUSH CACHE
__ENTITIES.description: Immediately saves the data buffers to disk.

__ENTITIES.name: GRAPH SETTINGS
__ENTITIES.syntax: GRAPH SETTINGS ( graphPicture ; xmin ; xmax ; ymin ; ymax ; xprop ; xgrid ; ygrid ; title {; title2 ; ... ; titleN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the graph settings for graph displayed in a form.

__ENTITIES.name: PAGE SETUP
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the page setup for the printer to that stored with form.

__ENTITIES.name: ORDER BY FORMULA
__ENTITIES.syntax: ORDER BY FORMULA ( aTable ; formula {; > or <}{; formula2 ; > or <2 ; ... ; formulaN ; > or <N} )
__ENTITIES.description: Sorts (reorders) the records of the current selection of aTable for the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: C_POINTER
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Pointer variable.

__ENTITIES.name: BREAK LEVEL
__ENTITIES.description: Specifies the number of break levels in a report performed using PRINT SELECTION.

__ENTITIES.name: ACCUMULATE
__ENTITIES.description: Specifies the fields or variables to be accumulated during a form report performed using PRINT SELECTION.

__ENTITIES.name: Get pointer
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the process or interprocess variable whose name you pass in varName.

__ENTITIES.name: C_BOOLEAN
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Boolean variable.

__ENTITIES.name: C_TIME
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Time variable.

__ENTITIES.name: C_DATE
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a Date variable.

__ENTITIES.name: Self
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the object whose object method is currently being executed.

__ENTITIES.name: SET AUTOMATIC RELATIONS
__ENTITIES.description: Temporarily changes all the manual relations into automatic relations for the entire database in the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: IDLE
__ENTITIES.description: Allows the 4D engine to be queried as part of an ON EVENT CALL in compiled mode

__ENTITIES.name: OPEN DATA FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Allows changing the data file opened by the 4D application on-the-fly.

__ENTITIES.name: CREATE DATA FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new data file to disk and replaces the data file opened by the 4D application on-the-fly.

__ENTITIES.name: Modified record
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if the current record of aTable has been modified but not saved; otherwise it returns False.

__ENTITIES.name: Is nil pointer
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if the pointer you pass in aPointer is Nil (->[]).

__ENTITIES.name: SET ABOUT
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the About 4D menu command in the Help (Windows) or in the Application (Mac OS X) menu to itemText.

__ENTITIES.name: New process
__ENTITIES.syntax: New process ( method ; stack {; name {; param {; param2 ; ... ; paramN}}}{; *} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Starts a new process (on the same machine) and returns the process number for that process.

__ENTITIES.name: PAUSE PROCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Suspends the execution of process until it is reactivated by the RESUME PROCESS command.

__ENTITIES.name: RESUME PROCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Resumes a process whose execution has been paused or delayed.

__ENTITIES.name: FILTER EVENT
__ENTITIES.description: Removes the current event (i.e., click, keystroke) from the event queue, so 4D will not perform any additional treatment to the one you made in the event-handling project method.

__ENTITIES.name: Current process
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the process reference number of the process within which this command is called.

__ENTITIES.name: DELAY PROCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Delays the execution of a process for a number of ticks (1 tick = 1/60th of a second)

__ENTITIES.name: HIDE PROCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Hides all windows that belong to process.

__ENTITIES.name: SHOW PROCESS
__ENTITIES.description: Displays all the windows belonging to process.

__ENTITIES.name: BRING TO FRONT
__ENTITIES.description: Brings all the windows belonging to process to the front.

__ENTITIES.name: Frontmost process
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of the process whose window (or windows) are in the front.

__ENTITIES.name: Outside call
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True for the After execution cycle

__ENTITIES.name: POST OUTSIDE CALL
__ENTITIES.description: Calls the form displayed in the frontmost window of process.

__ENTITIES.name: Process state
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the state of the process whose number you pass in process.

__ENTITIES.name: COPY NAMED SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Copies the current selection of aTable to the named selection name.

__ENTITIES.name: USE NAMED SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Uses the named selection name as the current selection for the table to which it belongs.

__ENTITIES.name: CLEAR NAMED SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Clears name from memory and frees the memory used by name.

__ENTITIES.name: CUT NAMED SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a named selection name and moves the current selection of aTable to it.

__ENTITIES.name: Count tasks
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the highest alive process number in the 4D single-user, 4D remote, or 4D Server (stored procedures) version.

__ENTITIES.name: PROCESS PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: PROCESS PROPERTIES ( process ; procName ; procState ; procTime {; procMode {; uniqueID {; origin}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns various information about the process whose process number you pass in process.

__ENTITIES.name: User in group
__ENTITIES.syntax: User in group ( user ; group ) -> Boolean
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if user is in group.

__ENTITIES.name: DISTINCT VALUES
__ENTITIES.description: Creates and populates the array array with non-repeated (unique) values coming from the field aField for the current selection of the table to which the field belongs and, optionally, returns the number of occurrences of each value in the countArray parameter.

__ENTITIES.name: RELATE MANY SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Generates a selection of records in the Many table, based on a selection of records in the One table, and loads the first record of the Many table as the current record.

__ENTITIES.name: QUERY SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Looks for records in aTable.

__ENTITIES.name: Count users
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of users connected to the server machine.

__ENTITIES.name: Count user processes
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the current number of "live" processes in the 4D application whose type is different from -25 (Internal Timer Process), -31 (Client Manager Process) and -15 (Server Interface Process)

__ENTITIES.name: SET INDEX
__ENTITIES.description: Creates or removes an index according to the parameters passed

__ENTITIES.name: SELECT LOG FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Creates, or closes the log file according to the value you pass in logFile.

__ENTITIES.name: Activated
__ENTITIES.description: (obsolete) returns True in a form method when the window containing the form becomes the frontmost window of the frontmost process.

__ENTITIES.name: Deactivated
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True in a form or object method when the frontmost window of the frontmost process moves to the back

__ENTITIES.name: SET MENU ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET MENU ITEM ( menu ; menuItem ; itemText {; process}{; *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the text of the menu item whose menu number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem, to the text passed in itemText.

__ENTITIES.name: RELATE ONE SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new selection of records for the table oneTable, based on the selection of records in the table manyTable and loads the first record of the new selection as the current record.

__ENTITIES.name: SCAN INDEX
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a selection of number records from the table containing the aField field

__ENTITIES.name: REDUCE SELECTION
__ENTITIES.description: Reduces the current selection of aTable to the first number records

__ENTITIES.name: LOCKED BY
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the user and process that have locked a record.

__ENTITIES.name: Picture size
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the size of picture in bytes.

__ENTITIES.name: Read only state
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the state of aTable is read-only and FALSE if the state of aTable is read/ write

__ENTITIES.name: Current default table
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a pointer to the table that has been passed to the last call to DEFAULT TABLE for the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: SET PRINT PREVIEW
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to programmatically check or uncheck the Preview on Screen option of the Print dialog box.

__ENTITIES.name: SELECTION RANGE TO ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: SELECTION RANGE TO ARRAY ( start ; end {; aField | aTable ; array} {; aField | aTable2 ; array2 ; ... ; aField | aTableN ; arrayN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates one or more arrays and copies data from the fields or record numbers from the current selection into the arrays.

__ENTITIES.name: Trigger event
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a numeric value that denotes the type of the database event, in other words, the reason why the trigger has been invoked.

__ENTITIES.name: SET PROCESS VARIABLE
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET PROCESS VARIABLE ( process ; dstVar ; expr {; dstVar2 ; expr2 ; ... ; dstVarN ; exprN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the dstVar process variables (dstVar2, etc.) of the destination process whose number is passed in process using the values passed in expr1 (expr2, etc.).

__ENTITIES.name: GET PROCESS VARIABLE
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET PROCESS VARIABLE ( process ; srcVar ; dstVar {; srcVar2 ; dstVar2 ; ... ; srcVarN ; dstVarN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Reads the srcVar process variables (srvVar2, etc.) from the source process whose number is passed in process, and returns their current values in the dstVar variables ( dstVar2, etc.) of the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: Process number
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of the process whose name you pass in name.

__ENTITIES.name: Execute on server
__ENTITIES.syntax: Execute on server ( procedure ; stack {; name {; param {; param2 ; ... ; paramN}}}{; *} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Starts a new process on the Server machine (if it is called in Client/Server) or on the same machine (if it is called in single-user) and returns the process number for that process.

__ENTITIES.name: New list
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new, empty hierarchical list in memory and returns its unique list reference number.

__ENTITIES.name: APPEND TO LIST
__ENTITIES.syntax: APPEND TO LIST ( list ; itemText ; itemRef {; sublist ; expanded} )
__ENTITIES.description: Appends a new item to the hierarchical list whose list reference number you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: CLEAR LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the hierarchical list whose list reference number you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: GET LIST ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET LIST ITEM ( {* ;} list ; itemPos | * ; itemRef ; itemText {; sublist ; expanded} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the item specified by itemPos of the list whose reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: Selected list items
__ENTITIES.syntax: Selected list items ( {* ;} list {; itemsArray {; *}} )  -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the position or reference of the selected item in the list whose reference number or object name you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: Count list items
__ENTITIES.description: Returns either the number of items currently “visible” or the total number of items in the list whose reference number or object name you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: SELECT LIST ITEMS BY POSITION
__ENTITIES.syntax: SELECT LIST ITEMS BY POSITION ( {* ;} list ; itemPos {; positionsArray} )
__ENTITIES.description: Selects the item(s) whose position is passed in itemPos and, optionally, in positionsArray within the list whose reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: Load list
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new hierarchical list whose contents are copied from the list and whose name you pass in listName.

__ENTITIES.name: SAVE LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Saves the list whose reference number you pass in list, within the Design environment List Editor, under the name you pass in listName.

__ENTITIES.name: SET LIST ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET LIST ITEM ( {* ;} list ; itemRef | * ; newItemText ; newItemRef {; sublist ; expanded} )
__ENTITIES.description: Modifies the item designated by the itemRef parameter within the list whose reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: SET LIST ITEM PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET LIST ITEM PROPERTIES ( {* ;} list ; itemRef | * ; enterable ; styles ; icon {; color} )
__ENTITIES.description: Modifies the item designated by the itemRef parameter within the list whose reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: SET LIST PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET LIST PROPERTIES ( list ; appearance {; icon {; lineHeight {; doubleClick {; multiSelections {; editable}}}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the line height and selection properties of the hierarchical list whose list reference you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: Form event
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a numeric value identifying the type of form event that has just occurred.

__ENTITIES.name: FILTER KEYSTROKE
__ENTITIES.description: Enables you to replace the character entered by the user into a field or an enterable area with the first character of the string filteredChar you pass.

__ENTITIES.name: Keystroke
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the character entered by the user into a field or an enterable area.

__ENTITIES.name: SORT LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Sorts the list whose reference number is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: SET DEFAULT CENTURY
__ENTITIES.description: Specifies the default century and the pivot year used by 4D when you enter a date with only two digits for the year.

__ENTITIES.name: Add to date
__ENTITIES.syntax: Add to date ( date ; years ; months ; days ) -> Date
__ENTITIES.description: Adds years, months, and days to the date you pass in aDate, then returns the result.

__ENTITIES.name: RESOLVE POINTER
__ENTITIES.syntax: RESOLVE POINTER ( aPointer ; varName ; tableNum ; fieldNum )
__ENTITIES.description: Retrieves the information of the object referenced by the pointer expression aPointer and returns it into the parameters varName, tableNum, and fieldNum.

__ENTITIES.name: SET QUERY LIMIT
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to tell 4D to stop any subsequent query for the current process as soon as at least the number of records you pass in limit has been found.

__ENTITIES.name: SET QUERY DESTINATION
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET QUERY DESTINATION ( destinationType {; destinationObject {; destinationPtr}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Enables you to tell 4D where to put the result of any subsequent query for the current process

__ENTITIES.name: In transaction
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the current process is in a transaction, otherwise it returns FALSE.

__ENTITIES.name: Trigger level
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the execution level of the trigger.

__ENTITIES.name: TRIGGER PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: TRIGGER PROPERTIES ( triggerLevel ; dbEvent ; tableNum ; recordNum )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the trigger execution level you pass in triggerLevel.

__ENTITIES.name: Pasteboard data size
__ENTITIES.description: Checks whether there is any data of the type you passed in dataType present in the pasteboard.

__ENTITIES.name: GET PASTEBOARD DATA
__ENTITIES.description: Returns, in the BLOB field or in the data variable, the data present in the pasteboard and whose type you pass in dataType.

__ENTITIES.name: CLEAR PASTEBOARD
__ENTITIES.description: Clears the pasteboard of all its contents.

__ENTITIES.name: APPEND DATA TO PASTEBOARD
__ENTITIES.syntax: APPEND DATA TO PASTEBOARD ( dataType ; data )
__ENTITIES.description: Appends to the pasteboard the data contained in the BLOB data under the data type specified in dataType.

__ENTITIES.name: Count menus
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of menus present in the menu bar.

__ENTITIES.name: Count menu items
__ENTITIES.syntax: Count menu items ( menu {; process} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of menu items present in the menu whose number or reference is passed in menu.

__ENTITIES.name: Create menu
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new menu in memory.

__ENTITIES.name: APPEND MENU ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: APPEND MENU ITEM ( menu ; itemText {; subMenu {; process {; *}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Appends new menu items to the menu whose number or reference is passed in menu.

__ENTITIES.name: INSERT MENU ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: INSERT MENU ITEM ( menu ; afterItem ; itemText {; subMenu {; process}}{; *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Inserts new menu items into the menu whose number or reference is passed in menu after the existing menu item whose number is passed in afterItem.

__ENTITIES.name: DELETE MENU ITEM
__ENTITIES.syntax: DELETE MENU ITEM ( menu ; menuItem {; process} )
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the menu item whose menu number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem.

__ENTITIES.name: Get menu item
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get menu item ( menu ; menuItem {; process} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the text of the menu item whose menu and item numbers are passed in menu and menuItem.

__ENTITIES.name: SET MENU ITEM SHORTCUT
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET MENU ITEM SHORTCUT ( menu ; menuItem ; itemKey ; modifiers {; process} )
__ENTITIES.description: Replaces the shortcut key associated with the menu command specified by menu and menuItem, by the character whose character code or text is passed in itemKey.

__ENTITIES.name: Get menu item key
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get menu item key ( menu ; menuItem {; process} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the code of the Ctrl (Windows) or Command (Macintosh) shortcut for the menu item whose menu number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem.

__ENTITIES.name: SET MENU ITEM STYLE
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET MENU ITEM STYLE ( menu ; menuItem ; itemStyle {; process} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the font style of the menu item whose menu number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem according to the font style passed in itemStyle.

__ENTITIES.name: Get menu item style
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get menu item style ( menu ; menuItem {; process} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the font style of the menu item whose number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem.

__ENTITIES.name: Get menu item mark
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get menu item mark ( menu ; menuItem {; process} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the check mark of the menu item whose number or reference is passed in menu and whose item number is passed in menuItem.

__ENTITIES.name: Get menu title
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get menu title ( menu {; process} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the title of the menu whose number or reference is passed in menu.

__ENTITIES.name: SHOW MENU BAR
__ENTITIES.description: Makes the menu bar visible.

__ENTITIES.name: HIDE MENU BAR
__ENTITIES.description: Makes the menu bar invisible.

__ENTITIES.name: SHOW TOOL BAR
__ENTITIES.description: Handles the display of custom toolbars created by the Open form window command for the current process

__ENTITIES.name: HIDE TOOL BAR
__ENTITIES.description: Handles the display of custom toolbars created by the Open form window command for the current process

__ENTITIES.name: SHOW WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Displays the window whose number was passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: HIDE WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Hides the window whose number was passed in window or, if this parameter is omitted, the current process frontmost window.

__ENTITIES.name: Count screens
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of screen monitors connected to your machine.

__ENTITIES.name: SCREEN COORDINATES
__ENTITIES.syntax: SCREEN COORDINATES ( left ; top ; right ; bottom {; screen} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns in left, top, right, and bottom the global coordinates of the screen specified by screen.

__ENTITIES.name: SCREEN DEPTH
__ENTITIES.description: Returns in depth and color information about the monitor.

__ENTITIES.name: Menu bar height
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the height of the menu bar, expressed in pixels.

__ENTITIES.name: Menu bar screen
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of the screen where the menu bar is located.

__ENTITIES.name: WINDOW LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the array windows with the window reference numbers of the windows currently open in all running processes (kernel or user processes).

__ENTITIES.name: GET WINDOW RECT
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET WINDOW RECT ( left ; top ; right ; bottom {; window} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the coordinates of the window whose reference number is passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: SET WINDOW RECT
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET WINDOW RECT ( left ; top ; right ; bottom {; window}{; *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the global coordinates of the window whose reference number is passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: Window kind
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the 4D type of the window whose reference number is passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: Window process
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the process number that runs the window whose reference number is passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: Frontmost window
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the window reference number of the frontmost window.

__ENTITIES.name: Next window
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the window reference number of the window “behind” the window you pass in window (based on the front-to-back order of the windows).

__ENTITIES.name: Find window
__ENTITIES.syntax: Find window ( left ; top {; windowPart} ) -> WinRef
__ENTITIES.description: Returns (if any) the reference number of the first window “touched” by the point whose coordinates passed in left and top.

__ENTITIES.name: Get window title
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the title of the window whose reference number is passed in window. If the window does not exist, an empty string is returned.

__ENTITIES.name: DRAG WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Lets users drag the window on which they clicked following the movements of the mouse.

__ENTITIES.name: MAXIMIZE WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Triggers the expansion of the window whose reference number was passed in window.

__ENTITIES.name: MINIMIZE WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the size of the window whose number is passed as window to the size it was before being maximized.

__ENTITIES.name: REDRAW WINDOW
__ENTITIES.description: Provokes a graphical update of the window whose reference number you pass in window.

__ENTITIES.name: PICTURE PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: PICTURE PROPERTIES ( picture ; width ; height {; hOffset {; vOffset {; mode}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the picture you pass in picture.

__ENTITIES.name: Tickcount
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of ticks (60th of a second) elapsed since the machine was started.

__ENTITIES.name: Milliseconds
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of milliseconds (1000th of a second) elapsed since the machine was started.

__ENTITIES.name: FONT LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the fonts text array with the names of scalable fonts available on your system.

__ENTITIES.name: POST KEY
__ENTITIES.description: Simulates a keystroke.

__ENTITIES.name: POST CLICK
__ENTITIES.description: Simulates a mouse click. Its effect as if the user actually clicked the mouse button.

__ENTITIES.name: POST EVENT
__ENTITIES.syntax: POST EVENT ( what ; message ; when ; mouseX ; mouseY ; modifiers {; process} )
__ENTITIES.description: Simulates a keyboard or mouse event.

__ENTITIES.name: GET MOUSE
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the current state of the mouse.

__ENTITIES.name: SET CURSOR
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the mouse cursor to the system cursor whose ID number you pass in cursor.

__ENTITIES.name: VOLUME LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the text array volumes with the names of the volumes currently defined (Windows) or mounted (Macintosh) on your machine.

__ENTITIES.name: VOLUME ATTRIBUTES
__ENTITIES.syntax: VOLUME ATTRIBUTES ( volume ; size ; used ; free )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns, expressed in bytes, the size, the used space and the free space for the volume whose name you pass in volume.

__ENTITIES.name: FOLDER LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the Text or String array directories with the names of the folders located at the pathname you pass in pathname.

__ENTITIES.name: DOCUMENT LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the Text array documents with the names of the documents located at the location you pass in pathname.

__ENTITIES.name: CREATE FOLDER
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a folder according to the pathname you pass in folderPath.

__ENTITIES.name: Test path name
__ENTITIES.description: Checks if a document or folder whose name or pathname you pass in pathname is present on the disk

__ENTITIES.name: GET DOCUMENT PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET DOCUMENT PROPERTIES ( document ; locked ; invisible ; created on ; created at ; modified on ; modified at )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the document whose name or pathname you pass in document.

__ENTITIES.name: SET DOCUMENT PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET DOCUMENT PROPERTIES ( document ; locked ; invisible ; created on ; created at ; modified on ; modified at )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the information about the document whose name or pathname you pass in document.

__ENTITIES.name: Get document size
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the size, expressed in bytes, of a document.

__ENTITIES.name: SET DOCUMENT SIZE
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the size of a document to the number of bytes you pass in size.

__ENTITIES.name: Get document position
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the position, starting from the beginning of the document, where the next read (RECEIVE PACKET) or write (SEND PACKET) will occur.

__ENTITIES.name: SET DOCUMENT POSITION
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET DOCUMENT POSITION ( docRef ; offset {; anchor} )
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the position you pass in offset where the next read (RECEIVE PACKET) or write (SEND PACKET) will occur.

__ENTITIES.name: Current machine
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the machine as set in the network parameters of the operating system.

__ENTITIES.name: Current system user
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the owner name of your machine, as set in the current user account on the machine.

__ENTITIES.name: Get 4D folder
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the pathname to the active 4D folder of the current application, or to the 4D environment folder specified by the folder parameter, if passed.

__ENTITIES.name: Temporary folder
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the pathname to the current temporary folder set by your system.

__ENTITIES.name: System folder
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the pathname to a particular folder of the operating system or to the active Windows or Mac OS System folder itself.

__ENTITIES.name: Structure file
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the long name of the structure file for the database with which you are currently working.

__ENTITIES.name: Data file
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the long name of the data file for the database with which you are currently working.

__ENTITIES.name: Application file
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the long name of the 4D executable file or application you are running.

__ENTITIES.name: Is compiled mode
__ENTITIES.description: Tests whether you are running in compiled mode (True) or interpreted mode (False).

__ENTITIES.name: Application version
__ENTITIES.description: Returns an encoded string value that expresses the version number of the 4D environment you are running.

__ENTITIES.name: Application type
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a numeric value that denotes the type of 4D environment that you are running.

__ENTITIES.name: Version type
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a numeric value that denotes the type of 4D or 4D Server version that you are running.

__ENTITIES.name: Open resource file
__ENTITIES.syntax: Open resource file ( resFilename {; fileType} ) -> DocRef
__ENTITIES.description: Opens the resource file whose name or pathname you pass in resFileName.

__ENTITIES.name: CLOSE RESOURCE FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Closes the resource file whose reference number is passed in resFile.

__ENTITIES.name: RESOURCE TYPE LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the array resTypes with the resource types of the resources present in the resource files currently open.

__ENTITIES.name: RESOURCE LIST
__ENTITIES.syntax: RESOURCE LIST ( resType ; resIDs ; resNames {; resFile} )
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the arrays resIDs and resNames with the resource IDs and names of the resources whose type is passed in resType.

__ENTITIES.name: GET PICTURE RESOURCE
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET PICTURE RESOURCE ( resID ; resData {; resFile} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns in the picture field or variable resData the picture stored in the picture (“PICT”) resource whose ID is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: Get text resource
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get text resource ( resID {; resFile} ) -> Text
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the text stored in the text (“TEXT”) resource whose ID is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: Get string resource
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get string resource ( resID {; resFile} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the string stored in the string (“STR ”) resource whose ID is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: GET RESOURCE
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET RESOURCE ( resType ; resID ; resData {; resFile} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns in the BLOB field or variable resData the contents of the resource whose type and ID is passed in resType and resID.

__ENTITIES.name: Get indexed string
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get indexed string ( resID ; strID {; resFile} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a string stored in an open XLIFF file whose 'id' attribute of the 'group' element is passed in resID or one of the strings stored in the string list (“STR#”) resource whose ID is passed in resID

__ENTITIES.name: STRING LIST TO ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: STRING LIST TO ARRAY ( resID ; strings {; resFile} )
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the array strings with a string stored in an open XLIFF file whose 'id' attribute of the 'group' element is passed in resID or the strings stored in the string list ("STR#") resource whose ID is passed in resID

__ENTITIES.name: Get resource name
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get resource name ( resType ; resID {; resFile} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the resource whose type is passed in resType and whose ID number is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: Get resource properties
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get resource properties ( resType ; resID {; resFile} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the attributes of the resource whose type is passed in resType and whose ID number is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: GET ICON RESOURCE
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET ICON RESOURCE ( resID ; resData {; fileRef} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns, in the picture field or variable resData, the icon stored in the color icon (“cicn”) resource whose ID is passed in resID.

__ENTITIES.name: SET PICTURE TO PASTEBOARD
__ENTITIES.description: Clears the pasteboard and puts a copy of the picture passed in picture into it.

__ENTITIES.name: GET PICTURE FROM PASTEBOARD
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the picture present in the pasteboard in the picture field or variable.

__ENTITIES.name: SET TEXT TO PASTEBOARD
__ENTITIES.description: Clears the pasteboard and then puts a copy of the text you passed in text into the pasteboard.

__ENTITIES.name: Get text from pasteboard
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the text present in the pasteboard.

__ENTITIES.name: DOCUMENT TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Loads the whole contents of document into blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB TO DOCUMENT
__ENTITIES.description: Rewrites the whole contents of document using the data stored in blob.

__ENTITIES.name: VARIABLE TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: VARIABLE TO BLOB ( variable ; blob {; offset | *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Stores the variable variable in the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB TO VARIABLE
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB TO VARIABLE ( blob ; variable {; offset} )
__ENTITIES.description: Rewrites the variable variable with the data stored within the BLOB blob at the byte offset (starting at zero) specified by offset.

__ENTITIES.name: COMPRESS BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Compresses the BLOB blob using a compression algorithm.

__ENTITIES.name: EXPAND BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Expands the BLOB blob that was previously compressed using the COMPRESS BLOB command.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB PROPERTIES ( blob ; compressed {; expandedSize {; currentSize}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: SET SCREEN DEPTH
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET SCREEN DEPTH ( depth {; color {; screen}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the depth and color/gray scale settings of the screen whose number you pass in screen.

__ENTITIES.name: Command name
__ENTITIES.syntax: Command name ( command {; info {; theme}} ) -> String
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name as well as (optionally) the properties of the command whose command number you pass in command.

__ENTITIES.name: Square root
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the square root of number.

__ENTITIES.name: MOVE DOCUMENT
__ENTITIES.description: Moves or renames a document.

__ENTITIES.name: COPY DOCUMENT
__ENTITIES.description: Copies the file or folder specified by sourceName to the location specified by destinationName and, optionally, renames it.

__ENTITIES.name: Pop up menu
__ENTITIES.syntax: Pop up menu ( contents {; default {; xCoord ; yCoord}} )  -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Displays a pop-up menu at the current location of the mouse.

__ENTITIES.name: Shift down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Shift key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: Macintosh control down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Macintosh Control key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: Macintosh option down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Macintosh Option key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: Macintosh command down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Macintosh command key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: Caps lock down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Caps Lock key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: INTEGER TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: INTEGER TO BLOB ( entier ; blob ; ordreOctet {; offset | *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the 2-byte Integer value integer into the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB to integer
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB to integer ( blob ; byteOrder {; offset} ) -> Integer
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a 2-byte Integer value read from the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: LONGINT TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: LONGINT TO BLOB ( longInt ; blob ; byteOrder {; offset | *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the 4-byte Long Integer value integer into the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB to longint
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB to longint ( blob ; byteOrder {; offset} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a 4-byte Long Integer value read from the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: REAL TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: REAL TO BLOB ( real ; blob ; realFormat {; offset | *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the Real value real into the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB to real
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB to real ( blob ; realFormat {; offset} ) -> Real
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a Real value read from the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: TEXT TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: TEXT TO BLOB ( text ; blob {; textFormat {; offset | *}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the Text value text into the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB to text
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB to text ( blob ; textFormat {; offset {; textLength}} )  -> Text
__ENTITIES.description: Returns a Text value read from the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: LIST TO BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Stores the hierarchical list list in the BLOB blob.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB to list
__ENTITIES.syntax: BLOB to list ( blob {; offset} ) -> ListRef
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new hierarchical list with the data stored within the BLOB blob at the byte offset (starting at zero) specified by offset and returns a List Reference number for that new list.

__ENTITIES.name: COPY BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: COPY BLOB ( srcBLOB ; dstBLOB ; srcOffset ; dstOffset ; len )
__ENTITIES.description: Copies the number of bytes specified by len from the BLOB srcBLOB to the BLOB dstBLOB.

__ENTITIES.name: INSERT IN BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: INSERT IN BLOB ( blob ; offset ; len {; filler} )
__ENTITIES.description: Inserts the number of bytes specified by len into the BLOB blob at the position specified by offset.

__ENTITIES.name: DELETE FROM BLOB
__ENTITIES.syntax: DELETE FROM BLOB ( blob ; offset ; len )
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the number of bytes specified by len from the BLOB blob at the position specified by offset

__ENTITIES.name: REMOVE FROM SET
__ENTITIES.description: Removes the current record of aTable from set.

__ENTITIES.name: Windows Ctrl down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Windows Ctrl key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: Windows Alt down
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the Windows Alt key is pressed.

__ENTITIES.name: PICTURE LIBRARY LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the reference numbers and names of the pictures currently stored in the Picture Library of the database.

__ENTITIES.name: GET PICTURE FROM LIBRARY
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET PICTURE FROM LIBRARY ( picRef | picName ; picture )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns in the picture parameter the Picture Library graphic whose reference number is passed in picRef or whose name is passed in picName.

__ENTITIES.name: SET PICTURE TO LIBRARY
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET PICTURE TO LIBRARY ( picture ; picRef ; picName )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates a new picture or replaces a picture in the Picture Library.

__ENTITIES.name: REMOVE PICTURE FROM LIBRARY
__ENTITIES.syntax: REMOVE PICTURE FROM LIBRARY ( picRef | picName )
__ENTITIES.description: Removes from the Picture Library the picture whose reference number is passed in picRef or whose name is passed in picName.

__ENTITIES.name: COPY SET
__ENTITIES.description: Copies the contents of the set srcSet into the set dstSet.

__ENTITIES.name: SET TABLE TITLES
__ENTITIES.description: Lets you mask, rename, and reorder the tables of your database that appear in standard 4D dialog boxes within the Application environment (when these editors are called using 4D language commands).

__ENTITIES.name: SET FIELD TITLES
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET FIELD TITLES ( aTable ; fieldTitles ; fieldNumbers {; *} )
__ENTITIES.description: Lets you mask, rename, and reorder the fields of the table passed in aTable or aSubtable when they appear in standard 4D dialog boxes, such as the Query editor, within the Application environment (more specifically, when the editors are called using 4D language commands).

__ENTITIES.name: OBJECT SET VISIBLE
__ENTITIES.description: Shows or hides the objects specified by object.

__ENTITIES.name: C_BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Casts each specified variable as a BLOB variable.

__ENTITIES.name: BLOB size
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the size of blob expressed in bytes.

__ENTITIES.name: SET BLOB SIZE
__ENTITIES.syntax: SET BLOB SIZE ( blob ; size {; filler} )
__ENTITIES.description: Resizes the BLOB blob according to the value passed in size.

__ENTITIES.name: DRAG AND DROP PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: DRAG AND DROP PROPERTIES ( srcObject ; srcElement ; srcProcess )
__ENTITIES.description: Enables you to obtain information about the source object when an On Drag Over or On Drop event occurs for a “complex” object (array, list box or hierarchical list).

__ENTITIES.name: Drop position
__ENTITIES.description: Can be used to find out the location, in a “complex” destination object, where an object has been (dragged and) dropped.

__ENTITIES.name: GET USER LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the arrays userNames and userNumbers with the names and unique ID numbers of the users as they appear in the Passwords window.

__ENTITIES.name: GET GROUP LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Populates the arrays groupNames and groupNumbers with the names and unique ID numbers of the groups as they appear in the Password editor window

__ENTITIES.name: GET USER PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET USER PROPERTIES ( userID ; name ; startup ; password ; nbLogin ; lastLogin {; memberships {; groupOwner}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the information about the user whose unique user ID number you pass in userID.

__ENTITIES.name: Set user properties
__ENTITIES.syntax: Set user properties ( userID ; name ; startup ; password ; nbLogin ; lastLogin {; memberships {; groupOwner}} ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Lets you change and update the properties of an existing user account whose unique user ID number you pass in userID, or add a new user affiliated with the Designer or the Administrator.

__ENTITIES.name: GET GROUP PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET GROUP PROPERTIES ( groupID ; name ; owner {; members} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the properties of the group whose unique group ID number you pass in groupID

__ENTITIES.name: Set group properties
__ENTITIES.syntax: Set group properties ( groupID ; name ; owner {; members} )  -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Enables you to change and update the properties of an existing group whose unique group ID number you pass in groupID, or to add a new group affiliated with the Designer or the Administrator

__ENTITIES.name: DELETE USER
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the user whose unique user ID number you pass in userID.

__ENTITIES.name: Is user deleted
__ENTITIES.description: Tests the user account whose unique user ID number you pass in userID.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB START SERVER
__ENTITIES.description: Starts the Web server of the 4D application on which it has been executed (4D or 4D Server)

__ENTITIES.name: WEB STOP SERVER
__ENTITIES.description: Stops the Web server of the 4D application on which it has been executed (4D ou 4D Server)

__ENTITIES.name: WEB SEND FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Sends, to the Web browser, the HTML page or the Web file stored in the document whose pathname you pass in htmlFile.

__ENTITIES.name: Is a list
__ENTITIES.description: Returns TRUE if the value you pass in list is a valid reference to a hierarchical list.

__ENTITIES.name: SET REAL COMPARISON LEVEL
__ENTITIES.description: Sets the epsilon value used by 4D to compare real values and expressions for equality.

__ENTITIES.name: DELETE FROM LIST
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the item designated by the itemRef parameter of the list whose reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: INSERT IN LIST
__ENTITIES.syntax: INSERT IN LIST ( {* ;} list ; beforeItemRef | * ; itemText ; itemRef {; sublist ; expanded} )
__ENTITIES.description: Inserts the item designated by the itemRef parameter in the list whose reference number or object name you pass in list.

__ENTITIES.name: Copy list
__ENTITIES.description: Duplicates the list whose reference number you pass in list, and returns the list reference number of the new list.

__ENTITIES.name: Current form table
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the pointer to the table of the form being displayed or printed in the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: OBJECT SET RGB COLORS
__ENTITIES.syntax: OBJECT SET RGB COLORS ( {* ;} object ; foregroundColor ; backgroundColor {; altBackgrndColor} )
__ENTITIES.description: Changes the foreground and background colors of the objects specified by the object parameter and the optional * parameter.

__ENTITIES.name: List item position
__ENTITIES.syntax: List item position ( {* ;} list ; itemRef ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the position of the item whose item reference number is passed in itemRef, within the list whose list reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: SELECT LIST ITEMS BY REFERENCE
__ENTITIES.syntax: SELECT LIST ITEMS BY REFERENCE ( list ; itemRef {; refArray} )
__ENTITIES.description: Selects the item(s) whose item reference number is passed in itemRef and, optionally, in refArray, within the list whose reference number is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: GET LIST ITEM PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET LIST ITEM PROPERTIES ( {* ;} list ; itemRef | * ; enterable {; styles {; icon {; color}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the properties of the item designated by the itemRef parameterwithin the list whose list reference number or object name is passed in list.

__ENTITIES.name: GET LIST PROPERTIES
__ENTITIES.syntax: GET LIST PROPERTIES ( list ; appearance {; icon {; lineHeight {; doubleClick {; multiSelections {; editable}}}}} )
__ENTITIES.description: Returns information about the list whose reference number you pass in list

__ENTITIES.name: List item parent
__ENTITIES.syntax: List item parent ( {* ;} list ; itemRef | * ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the item reference number of a parent item.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB SET ROOT FOLDER
__ENTITIES.description: Used to modify the default root folder where 4D looks for the HTML files requested of the Web server.

__ENTITIES.name: VARIABLE TO VARIABLE
__ENTITIES.syntax: VARIABLE TO VARIABLE ( process ; dstVar ; srcVar {; dstVar2 ; srcVar2 ; ... ; dstVarN ; srcVarN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Writes the dstVar process variables (dstVar2, etc.) of the destination process whose number is passed in process using the values of the variables srcVar1 srcVar2, etc.

__ENTITIES.name: CHANGE LICENSES
__ENTITIES.description: Displays the 4D License Manager dialog box

__ENTITIES.name: Validate password
__ENTITIES.syntax: Validate password ( userID ; password {; digest} ) -> Boolean
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if the string passed in password is the password for the user account whose ID number or name is passed in userID.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB SET HOME PAGE
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to modify the custom home page for the current Web process.

__ENTITIES.name: CREATE SELECTION FROM ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: CREATE SELECTION FROM ARRAY ( aTable ; recordArray {; selectionName} )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates the named selection selectionName from an array of absolute record numbers recordArray from aTable or an array of Booleans recordArray

__ENTITIES.name: CREATE SET FROM ARRAY
__ENTITIES.syntax: CREATE SET FROM ARRAY ( aTable ; recordsArray {; setName} )
__ENTITIES.description: Creates setName from an array of absolute record numbers recordsArray from aTable or an array of booleans recordsArray

__ENTITIES.name: SET DATABASE PARAMETER
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to modify various internal parameters of the 4D database.

__ENTITIES.name: Get database parameter
__ENTITIES.syntax: Get database parameter ( {aTable ;} selector {; stringValue} ) -> Real
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to get the current value of a 4D database parameter.

__ENTITIES.name: QUERY WITH ARRAY
__ENTITIES.description: Searches all the records for which the value of targetField is equal, at least, to one of the values of the elements in array.

__ENTITIES.name: SET TIMER
__ENTITIES.description: Activates the On Timer form event and sets, for the current form and process, the number of ticks elapsed between each On Timer form event.

__ENTITIES.name: BOOLEAN ARRAY FROM SET
__ENTITIES.syntax: BOOLEAN ARRAY FROM SET ( booleanArr {; set} )
__ENTITIES.description: Fills an array of Booleans indicating if each record in the table is or is not in set.

__ENTITIES.name: LONGINT ARRAY FROM SELECTION
__ENTITIES.syntax: LONGINT ARRAY FROM SELECTION ( aTable ; recordArray {; selection} )
__ENTITIES.description: Fills the recordArray array with the (absolute) record numbers that are in selection.

__ENTITIES.name: REGISTER CLIENT
__ENTITIES.description: “registers” a 4D client station with the name specified in clientName on 4D Server, so as to allow other clients or eventually 4D Server (by using stored methods) to execute methods on it by using the EXECUTE ON CLIENT command

__ENTITIES.name: UNREGISTER CLIENT
__ENTITIES.description: “unregisters” a 4D client station.

__ENTITIES.name: GET REGISTERED CLIENTS
__ENTITIES.description: Fills two arrays with the list of clients who were “registered” and the list of each client’s “workload”

__ENTITIES.name: EXECUTE ON CLIENT
__ENTITIES.syntax: EXECUTE ON CLIENT ( clientName ; methodName {; param}{; param2 ; ... ; paramN} )
__ENTITIES.description: Forces the execution of the methodName method, with the parameters param1... paramN, if necessary, on the registered 4D Client whose name is clientName.

__ENTITIES.name: Test semaphore
__ENTITIES.description: Tests for the existence of a semaphore.

__ENTITIES.name: Find in field
__ENTITIES.syntax: Find in field ( targetField ; value ) -> Longint
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the number of the first record whose targetField field is equal to value.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB SEND BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Allows you to send blob to the browser.

__ENTITIES.name: Get edited text
__ENTITIES.description: Retrieves the text as it is being entered in a form object

__ENTITIES.name: HIGHLIGHT RECORDS
__ENTITIES.description: Highlights records in a list form.

__ENTITIES.name: EXPORT DATA

__ENTITIES.name: Is new record

__ENTITIES.description: Displays a dialog box that allows you to manually select a folder and then retrieve the complete access path to that folder

__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if the process in which it is called is about to be interrupted unexpectedly, which means that the execution of the command was unable to reach its “normal” completion

__ENTITIES.description: Opens a new window using the size and resizing properties of the form formName.

__ENTITIES.description: Converts any value from and to the different currencies belonging to “Euroland” and the Euro currency itself.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB SEND TEXT
__ENTITIES.description: Directly sends HTML formatted text data.

__ENTITIES.name: READ PICTURE FILE
__ENTITIES.description: Opens the picture saved in the fileName disk file and loads it in the picture 4D field or variable.

__ENTITIES.description: Returns a thumbnail from a given source picture.

__ENTITIES.name: WRITE PICTURE FILE
__ENTITIES.syntax: WRITE PICTURE FILE ( fileName ; picture {; codec} )
__ENTITIES.description: Saves the picture passed in the picture parameter in the defined codec to disk.

__ENTITIES.description: Fills the text arrays nameArray and valueArray with the variable names and values contained in the Web form “submitted” (i.e. sent to the Web server).

__ENTITIES.name: Current method name

__ENTITIES.syntax: GET FIELD ENTRY PROPERTIES ( fieldPtr|tableNum {; fieldNum}; list ; mandatory ; nonEnterable ; nonModifiable )

__ENTITIES.description: Returns the properties for the table passed in tablePtr or tableNum.

__ENTITIES.name: GENERATE ENCRYPTION KEYPAIR

__ENTITIES.name: DECRYPT BLOB
__ENTITIES.description: Decrypts the content of the BLOB toDecrypt using the sender’s public key sendPubKey and, optionally, the recipient’s private key recipPrivKey.

__ENTITIES.name: PICTURE TO BLOB

__ENTITIES.description: Converts a picture stored in a 4D variable or field to another format and places the resulting picture in a BLOB.

__ENTITIES.name: DELETE FOLDER
__ENTITIES.description: Deletes the folder whose name or full path has been passed in folder.

__ENTITIES.name: CREATE ALIAS

__ENTITIES.name: RESOLVE ALIAS
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the full path to the target file or folder of the alias (named shortcut under Windows).

__ENTITIES.name: GET SERIAL INFORMATION

__ENTITIES.description: Returns various information about the 4D current version serialization.

__ENTITIES.name: WEB GET HTTP HEADER

__ENTITIES.description: Returns either a string or two arrays, containing the HTTP header used for the currently processed request.

__ENTITIES.name: GET DOCUMENT ICON

__ENTITIES.description: Returns the overall height (in pixels) of the section printed using the Print form command.

__ENTITIES.name: GET PRINTABLE AREA
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the size, in pixels, of the height and width parameters of the printable area.

__ENTITIES.name: Method called on error
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the method installed by the ON ERR CALL command for the current process.

__ENTITIES.name: Method called on event
__ENTITIES.description: Returns the name of the method installed by the ON EVENT CALL command.

__ENTITIES.description: Enables the definition of the marker position during printing.

__ENTITIES.description: Returns the current values of the different margins defined using the Print form, PRINT SELECTION and PRINT RECORD commands.

__ENTITIES.name: Contextual click
__ENTITIES.description: Returns True if a contextual click has been made

__ENTITIES.name: Is license available
__ENTITIES.description: Lets you find out the availability of a plug-in

__ENTITIES.description: Returns the bestWidth and bestHeight parameters, the “optimal” width and height of the form object designated by the * and object parameters.

__ENTITIES.name: MULTI SORT ARRAY

__ENTITIES.description: Enables you to carry out a multi-level sort on a set of arrays.

__ENTITIES.description: Returns a reference to the first “child” of the XML element passed in elementRef.

__ENTITIES.description: Returns a reference to the next “sibling” of the XML element passed as reference

__ENTITIES.description: Retrieves the output type of the report for the area whose reference was passed in area.

__ENTITIES.name: QR Get info row
